      "content": "That argument is a theoretical ideal that rarely plays out in the real world for small, local businesses. While increased spending is a nice concept, the immediate, tangible cost of higher labor is a fixed expense that must be covered first. The increased purchasing power of low-wage workers often doesn't fully compensate for the mandated wage increases, leading to inflationary pressure on goods and services. Ultimately, the burden of these mandates falls squarely on the local business owner.",
